$ cd ~
$ git clone https://github.com/yourusername/contract-review-app.git

(Replace with your actual GitHub repo URL)

4. Your files are now in: /home/[username]/contract-review-app/


STEP 3: INSTALL DEPENDENCIES (5 minutes)
────────────────────────────────────────

1. In the Bash console, navigate to your app:
   $ cd ~/contract-review-app

2. Create a virtual environment:
   $ mkvirtualenv contract-env --python=python3.10

3. Install requirements:
   $ pip install -r requirements.txt

4. Verify installation:
   $ pip list

You should see:
   • Flask
   • anthropic
   • pypdf
   • python-docx
   • Werkzeug


STEP 4: SET UP WEB APP (10 minutes)
───────────────────────────────────

1. Go back to dashboard, click "Web" tab
2. Click "Add a new web app"
3. Click "Next" (accept the domain name)
4. Choose "Flask"
5. Choose Python 3.10
6. Click "Next"
7. For path, enter: /home/[username]/contract-review-app/app.py
8. Click "Next"

Your web app is created!


STEP 5: CONFIGURE WSGI FILE (5 minutes)
───────────────────────────────────────

1. In the "Web" tab, find "Code" section
2. Click on the WSGI configuration file link (should be blue)
   Example: /var/www/username_pythonanywhere_com_wsgi.py

3. Delete ALL existing code in that file

4. Replace with this code:

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
import sys

# Add your project directory to the sys.path
project_home = '/home/[USERNAME]/contract-review-app'
if project_home not in sys.path:
    sys.path = [project_home] + sys.path

# Import your Flask app
from app import app as application
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

IMPORTANT: Replace [USERNAME] with your actual PythonAnywhere username!

5. Click "Save" (top right)


STEP 6: SET ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES (3 minutes)
─────────────────────────────────────────────

1. Still in "Web" tab, scroll down to "Environment variables"
2. Click "Start new env variable"
3. Add your API key:
   Name: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
   Value: [your actual API key from Anthropic]
4. Click "✓" to save

IMPORTANT: Never share your API key or commit it to GitHub!


STEP 7: SET VIRTUALENV (2 minutes)
──────────────────────────────────

1. In "Web" tab, find "Virtualenv" section
2. Enter path to your virtual environment:
   /home/[username]/.virtualenvs/contract-env
3. It should turn green if path is correct


STEP 8: RELOAD & TEST (2 minutes)
─────────────────────────────────

1. At the top of "Web" tab, click the big green "Reload" button
2. Wait 10 seconds
3. Click on your app URL: [username].pythonanywhere.com
